[
    {
        "content": "<p>I propose that we have the formatter add a space in front of the <code>.</code> in static-dispatch function calls (and the <code>-&gt;</code> in local-dispatch ones).</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># current</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Aaaaaa</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bbbbbb</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Aaaaaa</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cccccc</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">qux</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">eee</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">fff</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ggg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># proposal</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Aaaaaa</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bbbbbb</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Aaaaaa</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cccccc</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">qux</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">eee</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">fff</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ggg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Our current approach to whitespace and periods seems to be that only a newline prefix is <strong><em>optional</em></strong> for readability:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bar</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">baz</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Aaaaaa</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bbbbbb</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Aaaaaa</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cccccc</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">qux</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">eee</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">fff</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ddd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ggg</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, <strong><em>I'm concerned about the readability of the dense one-line chains</em></strong> that we may be encouraging (that I already see regularly in examples that folks post in here).</p>\n<p>Here's an example <a href=\"https://github.com/JanCVanB/roc-realworld/commit/859aad1d50773f134e63ae8b790ccd67d38ca60e#diff-7d7465c4ffb135df45b1c56e3ec13b241ffe583417df09c6bb88a1e8e34766ffR30-R32\">from roc-realworld</a> (with the first line modified to use local function dispatch, though that could improve all these lines):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># current</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_json!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># proposal</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_json!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(see <a href=\"https://github.com/JanCVanB/roc-realworld/tree/spaced_dispatch\">my branch with these spaces added to all dispatches</a>)</p>\n<p>To me, this</p>\n<ul>\n<li>helps prevent post-arg-comma spaces from dominating the visual structure of dispatch-heavy lines.</li>\n<li>ensures a helpful visual pause before the slight context shift from each datum to its next transform.</li>\n<li>injects some FP/ML flair into traditional method-y chains. (It kind of feels like an opportunity to preserve the visual pleasure of WSA, but that's not my motivator.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>While this would surely consume a little of our strangeness budget, it seems intuitive and worth it! What do you think?</p>",
        "id": 502731781,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740823818
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p><em>I'm concerned about the readability of the dense one-line chains</em></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I share the concern, the space before does look weird to me though. I would rather force more newlines, but Richard does not like that :p</p>",
        "id": 502732354,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1740824378
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I understand Richard's concern for fighting with the formatter, but allowing the kind of density like in Jan's auth snippet (before) would be a big mistake in my opinion.</p>",
        "id": 502732604,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1740824571
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just now scrolled up through all <a class=\"stream\" data-stream-id=\"304641\" href=\"/#narrow/channel/304641-ideas\">#ideas</a> posts in February, and I was surprised to see basically zero multi-dispatch one-liners to quote+spaceify here. I suppose the offensively-dense ones I'm remembering were from earlier.</p>",
        "id": 502734529,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740826131
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I did see this, though, which has become almost a must-include in topics proposing changes related to dispatch syntax:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># current</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">hours</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">ago!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># proposal</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">hours</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">ago!</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502734750,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740826319
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The <code>roc-realworld</code> example seems much easier to improve in a non-pioneering way with newlines instead of space-separated method calls</p>",
        "id": 502734882,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740826400
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>\"pioneering\" meaning the exploration of a syntax that I've not seen in another language before</p>",
        "id": 502734922,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740826435
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># with newlines instead (idk if the braces are required)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_json!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">req</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502735156,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740826636
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I meant between the methods</p>",
        "id": 502735171,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740826656
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah I misclicked enter :P</p>",
        "id": 502735304,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740826780
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That's extremely readable to me, I think the question would then be \"when do we <em>force</em> newlines\"</p>",
        "id": 502735393,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740826836
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Because I think with short method names, three calls in a row can be totally reasonable:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">build_color</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">color</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502735476,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740826918
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>vs</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">build_color</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">color</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>or <em>(added after Sam's next message)</em></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">build_color</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"nf\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">color</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">r</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">g</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502735584,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740826988
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Totally subjectively, it seems like a minor readability improvement for a marked (no one else does this) weirdness cost</p>",
        "id": 502735696,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827071
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree it's not critical for short one-liners. My concern is mostly when commas and/or nesting are involved, which has subjectively felt frequent.</p>",
        "id": 502735766,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740827139
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I share the same concern</p>",
        "id": 502735853,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827177
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would need strong convincing that we can't solve this problem with the existing solution of newlines</p>",
        "id": 502735902,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827216
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But in general, Roc takes the learning from Elm that you can communicate control flow rough shape with newlines and tab depth</p>",
        "id": 502735971,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827279
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And those method chains are just Dark Bramble</p>",
        "id": 502736031,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827300
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would you prefer the formatter enforce a newline prefix with dispatch, at least for \"longer\" chains like in the realworld quote above?</p>",
        "id": 502736077,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740827372
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, for <code>.</code> and for <code>-&gt;</code></p>",
        "id": 502736199,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827453
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would that solve your concern if we found the magic rule of when to apply that?</p>",
        "id": 502736230,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827491
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would </p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"462053\">JanCVanB</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/304641-ideas/topic/formatting.20space.20in.20static.20dispatch/near/502731781\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># before</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_json!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"c1\"># after</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_json!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I'd say that the spaces don't help me de-kudzu this example, but maybe it's readable to you? I think newlines are necessary for readability here</p>",
        "id": 502736341,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740827580
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One upside of static dispatch that I've seen Richard celebrate on multiple occasions is being able to view more code without scrolling, so I doubt that 4x-ing the LOC count of business logic is actually an option he'd go for. (Though it would only expand dense spots with no decrease in concision.) My goal here was to propose something that doesn't reopen any LOC explosion fears, but that might be a necessary consideration.</p>",
        "id": 502737137,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740828265
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In my eyes, density is the root of the problem</p>",
        "id": 502737186,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740828310
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So managing density is what's required if that's the case</p>",
        "id": 502737212,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740828335
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure the formatter should really have an opinion here. These aren't even long chains.  I think we should say if there is a newline before any of the accesses, we newline them all.  But this example just needs newlines I think for most people.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Ruby\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">authenticate</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"no\">Auth</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">auth_optional</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">req</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">now!</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_json!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">req</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">decode</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"no\">Json</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">utf8</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">and_then!</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle!</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"o\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"n\">to_resp</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But I'm not convinced the formatter should enforce this.</p>",
        "id": 502739208,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740829967
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The above is at least readable and consistent, you can see each step without worrying about creating a block or creating named variables(the real value of a pipeline)</p>",
        "id": 502739318,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740830057
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I agree that it'll be very hard to come up with a simple but non-aggravating rule for the formatter to add newlines</p>",
        "id": 502740098,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740830707
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Which is why I'd not be in favor unless something like that is found</p>",
        "id": 502740115,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740830725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Clarification: My proposal specifically doesn't include accesses.</p>",
        "id": 502740199,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740830793
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(though I get what you're saying about newline consistency, Anthony)</p>",
        "id": 502740294,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740830878
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I stand by my proposal as compatible with whatever we decide about newlines, because it's specifically about handling the newline-less cases.</p>",
        "id": 502740423,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740831003
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"462053\">JanCVanB</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/formatting.20space.20in.20static.20dispatch/near/502740199\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Clarification: My proposal specifically doesn't include accesses.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That would run directly into the precedence issues that Richard had with pizza's interaction with methods right</p>",
        "id": 502740612,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1740831138
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think not, because it should still parse unambiguously and it's just for aesthetics, like the spaces we like after commas.</p>",
        "id": 502740743,
        "sender_full_name": "jan kili",
        "timestamp": 1740831278
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the weirdness budget cost on the spaces idea is prohibitively high in this case</p>",
        "id": 502741607,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740832042
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I think it's worth discussing the question of whether the formatter should enforce newlines</p>",
        "id": 502741682,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740832085
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in general, we historically have never enforced newlines anywhere</p>",
        "id": 502741700,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740832108
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>why would this be the first case where we should do that? <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 502741709,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740832124
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I believe that with the pizza operator nearly everyone chose to format things over multiple lines but <code>.</code> may not encourage this as much</p>",
        "id": 502742150,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1740832516
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And I think that is fine.  If someone is keeping it oneline, they've deemed that as a readable expression.  If we started having a formatter that enforces line lengths (using some variant of A Prettier Printer), I think we could then say easily that individual accesses would be a Group and flow to a newline (with or without a new level of indentation)</p>",
        "id": 502751063,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740839017
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>If someone is keeping it oneline, they've deemed that as a readable expression.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think the person who wrote the code can't judge this well, they've got a clear picture of what the code does in their mind. They will quickly believe the code is easy to understand.</p>",
        "id": 502762971,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1740846520
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Like with function arguments, function params, record fields, lists, and tuples where it is a decision of the user based on a trailing comma, I mostly think this fits as an ok decision of the user based on inserting a new line.</p>",
        "id": 502765726,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1740848332
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I do agree it is likely to lead to denser code than <code>|&gt;</code>. I think that is pretty obvious to see looking at other languages</p>",
        "id": 502765766,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1740848373
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think for anyone looking at the topic using their phone, you will be extra biased to want new lines. I also think that looking at this code with syntax highlighters on Zulip that do not match what roc syntax highlighting will look like will also lead to wanting more new lines.</p>",
        "id": 502766029,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1740848549
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To me, this really feels like a wait and see kind of issue</p>",
        "id": 502766057,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1740848578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Once there are 10s of thousands of lines of roc code on the new syntax, let's get a vibe check on density.</p>",
        "id": 502766089,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1740848617
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(tangent!) This actually brings up a slight syntax ambiguity. What if you have a function that you want to consist of two lines: (1) a statement, and then (2) returning a record accessor function.</p>\n<p>Something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>foo = |x| {\n    if x == 3 { return .a }\n    Stdout.write(&quot;Tried to do a thing ${x}&quot;)\n    .b\n}\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>How do we make sure that's not parsed as:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>foo = |x| {\n    if x == 3 { return .a }\n    Stdout.write(&quot;Tried to do a thing ${x}&quot;).b\n}\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 502796071,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1740869485
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>great point!</p>",
        "id": 502796610,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740869905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>an easy fix would be changing accessor syntax to be <code>_.b</code></p>",
        "id": 502796631,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740869933
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So no space? like <code>xyz.b</code>? </p>\n<p>edit: I guess that doesn't work with newlines</p>",
        "id": 502797949,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1740870994
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think the same thing also applies to the static-dispatch closures, e.g. the <code>.foo()</code> in <code>.values.map(.foo())</code></p>",
        "id": 502801818,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1740874166
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>indeed!</p>",
        "id": 502802940,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1740875135
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"281383\">Richard Feldman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/formatting.20space.20in.20static.20dispatch/near/502796631\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>an easy fix would be changing accessor syntax to be <code>_.b</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I was actually assuming we were doing this <span aria-label=\"rolling on the floor laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f923\" role=\"img\" title=\"rolling on the floor laughing\">:rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 502851993,
        "sender_full_name": "Anthony Bullard",
        "timestamp": 1740916088
    }
]